727054f-d.text:
Jamaica Ave., north side, between 165th and 166th Streets, in rear of 437-445 Jamaica Ave. (old nos.), showing in a set of four views the home of P. Wood in 1891.  At one time this property was owned by John N. Brinkerhoff.  This house was also the property of Hendrick Onderdonk Jr.; Maggie Bramhall, sister of T.F. Archer 2nd was another owner.  It was not in existence in 1931.

May 1923.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

165th Street, east side, between Janaica Avenue and 94th Avenue, viewing south from near the former toward the Long Island Railroad tracks and showing typical homes of old Jamaica. 165th Street, here, was formerly called Puntine Street.

P. L. Sperr
April 7, 1932
